model.description: Trace-level multi-agent tournament with adaptive role selection under incentive contexts.

reward_models.cooperative: group correctness + truthful trace + individual correctness
reward_models.competitive: individual correctness + influence - group correctness + deceptive bonus when group wrong

interpretation: Competitive incentives increased deceptor share in explicit per-trace multi-agent runs.
Competitive incentives reduced group accuracy relative to cooperative incentives.
This is software-agent live trace evidence; external/LLM human-task replication is still future work.
